A trigger is SQL code that runs automatically when something happens in a table.

Think:

“If something happens → execute code automatically”


| Action | Meaning        |
| ------ | -------------- |
| INSERT | adding data    |
| UPDATE | modifying data |
| DELETE | deleting data  |

Syntax:
 DELIMITER //

CREATE TRIGGER triggerName
BEFORE INSERT
ON tableName
FOR EACH ROW
BEGIN

   -- SQL code

END //

DELIMITER ;

Important Words  :
| Keyword      | Meaning               |
| ------------ | --------------------- |
| BEFORE       | before operation      |
| AFTER        | after operation       |
| INSERT       | add row               |
| UPDATE       | modify row            |
| DELETE       | remove row            |
| FOR EACH ROW | execute for every row |
  Inside triggers we use:
  | Keyword    | Meaning   |
| ---------- | --------- |
| NEW.column | new value |
| OLD.column | old value |
